FT  17 OCT 92 / UK Company News: Exceptional charge leaves Baris in loss
Legal costs and under-performance by its Spanish offshoot left Baris
Holdings, USM-quoted provider of fire protection, in the red in the six
months to the end of August.
The pre-tax loss was Pounds 70,000 after an exceptional charge of Pounds
358,000, relating to legal fees in a dispute over two contracts.
Turnover for the six months increased to Pounds 11.3m, against Pounds 11m
when pre-tax profits were Pounds 403,000.
Losses per share came out at 1p (earnings 3.7p) and the interim dividend is
being passed (2p).
